  <h1>
   room_set_camera
  </h1>
  With this function you can assign a camera to a specific viewport in a room other than the current one. You supply the room index, the view index (from 0 to 7) and then the index of the camera to use.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">room_set_camera(rm, vind, camera);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      rm
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Rooms.htm">
        Room Asset
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the room to set the view camera of
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      vind
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the view port to assign the camera to
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      camera
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Cameras_And_Display/Cameras_And_Viewports/camera_create.htm">
        Camera ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the camera to assign
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">global.myroom = room_add();
room_set_camera(global.myroom, 0, global.MainCam);
</code></pre>
  The above code assigns a camera in a newly created room to view port [0].
